  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empower &amp; Educate the Girls of Rural Kisumu</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A study sponsored by The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation found that approximately 65% of women and girls in Kenya are unable to afford sanitary pads. Other studies have shown that many girls drop out of school when they hit menarche and many miss up to 5 days of school every month.    Many girls  of the schools we work with stayed at home during their periods which led to absenteeism which meant they were always having to play catch-up at school. This then leads to many of them dropping out.</narrative>
  </description>
